<ITEM><PB N="iii" REF="5"><HI>Page</HI> 86. The great wickedness carried on by the Bri|tish nation, the cause of leading them into a world of debt&mdash;That debt a cause of oppression and slavery&mdash;The various instigators of it profligate and wicked men.</ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>Page</HI> 92. The Spanish barbarities imitated by other nations, and the infernal invention of slavery followed after&mdash;94. The sufferings of the Africans described.</ITEM>
